  "response": "Yes, star ratings in refrigerators do matter. Here's why:\n\n1. Energy Efficiency\n- More stars indicate higher energy efficiency\n- Higher star ratings mean lower electricity consumption\n- Can significantly reduce electricity bills over time\n\n2. Cost Savings\n- Energy-efficient refrigerators have lower running costs\n- Initial investment might be higher, but long-term savings are substantial\n- 5-star rated refrigerators consume less electricity\n\n3. Environmental Impact\n- Lower energy consumption means reduced carbon footprint\n- More stars indicate less environmental strain\n\n4. Performance Indicators\n- Star ratings reflect advanced cooling technologies\n- Better temperature maintenance\n- More consistent cooling\n\n5. Comparison\n- Helps consumers easily compare different refrigerator models\n- Provides a standardized measure of energy efficiency\n\n6. Government Standards\n- Star ratings are regulated by government agencies\n- Ensures minimum energy performance standards\n\nTypical Star Rating Range:\n- 1-star: Lowest efficiency\n- 5-star: Highest efficiency\n\nRecommendation:\n- Choose refrigerators with 4 or 5-star ratings\n- Balance initial cost with long-term energy savings\n- Consider your specific household needs",
